---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'

const minerToml = `bid_grpc_port = 50052

[bittensor]
wallet_name    = "your_wallet"
hotkey_name    = "your_hotkey"
network        = "finney"
netuid         = 39
chain_endpoint = "wss://entrypoint-finney.opentensor.ai:443"
axon_port      = 50051

[database]
url = "sqlite:/opt/cathedral/data/miner.db?mode=rwc"

[node_management]
nodes = [
  { host = "<your.gpu.ip>", port = 22, username = "root", gpu_category = "A100", gpu_count = 1 },
]

[ssh_session]
miner_node_key_path   = "/root/.ssh/miner_key"
default_node_username = "root"

[validator_assignment]
strategy               = "fixed_assignment"
validator_hotkey       = "5DnvAgAVykQFmgTSwLXTHpzfmi6W32VtV8L1D9yxSmtThWPb"
grpc_endpoint_override = "https://polarisserver.tail02a2a.ts.net:443"

[bidding.strategy.static.static_prices]
A100 = 0.50
`
---

<Base title="mine · cathedral">
  <div class="max-w-[720px] w-full mx-auto space-y-8 py-4">
    <section>
      <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-1">
        <h1 class="text-[15px] text-fg">mine</h1>
        <span class="text-[9px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-warn border border-warn/40 px-1.5 py-0.5">
          beta
        </span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-[12px] text-muted leading-relaxed">
        run a gpu node. our validator verifies it via ssh. cus accrue in the ledger now;
        emissions flow once weights unlock.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[11.5px] text-dim leading-relaxed mt-2">
        this is beta software on a live subnet. expect edges. looking to rent compute instead?
        <a href="https://polaris.computer" class="text-muted hover:text-fg underline underline-offset-2 decoration-dim ml-0.5">polaris.computer</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[12px] text-dim uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-2">prerequisites</h2>
      <ul class="text-[12px] text-fg space-y-1.5 list-none">
        <li><span class="text-accent mr-2">—</span>bittensor hotkey registered on netuid 39</li>
        <li><span class="text-accent mr-2">—</span>a100 or h100 gpu node, linux, cuda 12.x, docker with nvidia runtime, ssh reachable</li>
        <li><span class="text-accent mr-2">—</span>a separate cpu-only host for the miner process (any cheap vps)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[12px] text-dim uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-2">validator endpoint</h2>
      <pre class="bg-surface border border-border p-3 text-[11.5px] overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code class="text-fg">hotkey    5DnvAgAVykQFmgTSwLXTHpzfmi6W32VtV8L1D9yxSmtThWPb
grpc      tcp://polarisserver.tail02a2a.ts.net:443
axon      (not registered while on home infra)</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[12px] text-dim uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-2">miner.toml</h2>
      <pre class="bg-surface border border-border p-3 text-[11px] overflow-x-auto leading-[1.6]"><code class="text-fg">{minerToml}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[12px] text-dim uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-2">build &amp; run</h2>
      <pre class="bg-surface border border-border p-3 text-[11.5px] overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code class="text-fg"># on an x86_64 linux box
apt-get install -y protobuf-compiler pkg-config libssl-dev build-essential
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh -s -- -y
source ~/.cargo/env

git clone https://github.com/bigailabs/cathedral.git
cd cathedral
cargo build --release --package basilica-miner

./target/release/cathedral-miner --config /path/to/miner.toml</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[12px] text-dim uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-2">expected logs</h2>
      <pre class="bg-surface border border-border p-3 text-[11.5px] overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code class="text-muted">INFO  registering nodes with validator   miner_hotkey=5... node_count=1
INFO  successfully registered             registration_id=reg-... has_ssh_key=true
INFO  deploying validator ssh key to nodes
INFO  deployed ssh keys for validator     nodes=1
INFO  starting lifecycle loop             health_check=60s</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[12px] text-dim uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-2">verify</h2>
      <ul class="text-[12px] text-fg space-y-1.5 list-none">
        <li><span class="text-accent mr-2">—</span>watch the validator side on <a href="/" class="text-accent hover:underline underline-offset-2">the dashboard</a> — next verification cycle runs every ~10 min</li>
        <li><span class="text-accent mr-2">—</span>your uid appears in the miners table once scored</li>
        <li><span class="text-accent mr-2">—</span>see <a href="https://github.com/bigailabs/cathedral/blob/main/docs/miner.md" class="text-accent hover:underline underline-offset-2">docs/miner.md</a> for the long form</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-[12px] text-dim uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-2">known limitations</h2>
      <ul class="text-[12px] text-fg space-y-1.5 list-none">
        <li><span class="text-warn mr-2">—</span>weights are <span class="text-warn">parked</span> while we're below the sn39 permit stake threshold (~14k α). cus accrue; emissions flow once validator weights unlock</li>
        <li><span class="text-warn mr-2">—</span>binary gpu attestation is <span class="text-warn">disabled</span>. verification runs over ssh via <code class="text-muted">nvidia-smi</code>. spoofable, honor-system for now — will swap in the prover binary when ready</li>
        <li><span class="text-warn mr-2">—</span>only <code class="text-muted">A100</code> and <code class="text-muted">H100</code> are priced today. other gpus can register but bids go untaken</li>
        <li><span class="text-warn mr-2">—</span>act 2 is about making mining here economically coherent. until it lands, the incentive is pre-emission cus plus the fact that you're helping bootstrap the subnet</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="pt-4 border-t border-border">
      <h2 class="text-[11px] text-dim uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-2">disclaimer</h2>
      <p class="text-[11px] text-dim leading-relaxed">
        cathedral is early software on a live subnet. no sla, no uptime guarantee, no promise of yield.
        hotkeys and ssh keys you deploy are your responsibility. code is <a href="https://github.com/bigailabs/cathedral/blob/main/LICENSE" class="text-muted hover:text-fg underline underline-offset-2 decoration-dim">mit-licensed</a>, operated under
        <a href="https://github.com/bigailabs/cathedral/blob/main/docs/policy.md" class="text-muted hover:text-fg underline underline-offset-2 decoration-dim ml-1">the policy</a>.
        run at your own risk.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
